      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The state's mandates are not inherently biased; they are the codified agreements necessary for a pluralistic society to function peacefully. The legal system is designed to be neutral, meaning it applies rules equally, not to endorse one belief system over another. True religious freedom is best protected when it can be practiced without compelling others to violate their own conscience, which is why limitations are necessary when faith clashes with universal law.",
